              <table id="EditorialReviewsPanel" class="ReviewSection" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%"><tr><td>
	
                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Amazon.com:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1">Author Nicholas Lore uses the techniques of his career-guidance network, the Rockport Institute, to make <i>The Pathfinder</i> a substitute for a great job counselor. Through goal setting, list making, and other techniques, the book leads readers though the process of deciding exactly what they want to do for a living and finding a way to make it happen. Lore realizes that people have different temperaments and decision-making methods, so he provides individualized advice to suit each one. He also understands that creating a new career requires courage as well as desire, so <i>The Pathfinder</i> devotes plenty of space to motivation and overcoming fears. While anyone looking for a new career will find direction with this guide, people who didn't <i>know</i> they were looking may decide to start once they go through Lore's probing self-examination process. </span>
              
</td></tr></table>
              <table id="CustomerReviewsPanel" class="ReviewSection" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%"><tr><td>
	
