                      <span>2005-04-23</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>The Pathfinder does a great job of taking on the false idea that we need to stick to one career ladder in order to have successful, satisfying lives.  As a coach for Renaissance Souls (people with too many interests to pick just one)I was especially pleased Nicholas Lore was the author and creator of the exercises. Given his solid background with the Rockport Institute Career Choice Program, this book is great for parents/partners who doubt our inevitable need to change from one thing to another!</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">It's not just a book; it's a program.</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>6</span>
                      /
                      <span>7</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2005-03-21</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I completed the work in this book in 1997.  In the back of the book there are phone numbers for further research.  I completed a whole Pathfinders survey, did a phone interview and received a tape of it, and although I felt it was VERY expensive, ultimately, it did help me find a career that was a giant leap but an excellent fit with my needs and skills.  I listened to my own answers and suggestions on the tape, and can say they also helped me greatly to realize I knew what I wanted all along.  I am very happily ensconced in my career, and 8 years after I read this book, I can still say it helped to change my life.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Want career help that benefits you, not the author?</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>22</span>
